# Ruff and style

- **Line length**: Keep lines ≤ 88 characters (ruff E501). Fix by **breaking into multiple lines** (parentheses, backslash, or new string/statement), not by shortening text or comments.
- **Messages and user-facing strings**: Do not shorten or abbreviate messages, docstrings, or UI text to satisfy line length. Use line continuation or split across lines instead.
- **After edits**: Ensure changes are ruff-compliant (e.g. run `uv run ruff check .` or pre-commit) so the project stays within the configured 88-char limit.
